Dist_comm: Río Zuñac reserve of Fundación EcoMinga, adjacent to Llanganates National Park, ca. 5 km N of Baños-Mera highway.  Upper watershed of Río Zuñac.  Very wet cloud forest with abundant epiphytes, canopy 25 m; granite substrate. Marked trees  = 10 cm DBH in 0.25-hectare tree inventory plot, "Zuñac Plot # 3", on high ridge above river valley.  With students in the "Tropical Botany" field course, part of the project "Systematics and Evolution of the Neotropical clade of Schefflera s.l. (Araliaceae)", and the Recalde family park guards.
